parameters.name: FilterEndTime
parameters.description: The end time of the time range in which you want to track data operations. The time must be specified in the yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss format.

parameters.name: FilterStartTime
parameters.description: The start time of the time range in which you want to track data operations. The time must be specified in the yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss format.

parameters.name: FilterTableList
parameters.description: The names of the tables for which you want to track data operations.

parameters.name: FilterTypeList
parameters.description: The types of data operations that you want to track.

parameters.name: OrderId
parameters.description: The ID of the ticket. You can call the [ListOrders](~~144643~~) operation to obtain the ticket ID.

parameters.name: RollbackSQLType
parameters.description:
The type of the SQL statement.

*   **REVERSE**: undoes or rolls back an executed SQL statement, which is equivalent to the UNDO SQL statement.
*   **FORWARD**: redoes or re-executes an SQL statement that failed to be executed, which is equivalent to the REDO SQL statement.

parameters.name: Tid
parameters.description: The ID of the tenant. You can call the [GetUserActiveTenant](~~198073~~) or [ListUserTenants](~~198074~~) operation to query the tenant ID.
